==Ternate==
===Etymology===
From {{der|tft|ms|yang}}, from {{der|tft|ms-old|yaṃ}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|tft|[jaŋ]}}
===Conjunction===
{{tft-con|j=يڠ}}
# {{n-g|relative clause introducer}}; [[which]], [[that]]
#: {{syn|tft|ma}}
#: {{uxi|tft|pangkat '''yang''' gaku|t=a high position|lit=a position '''which is''' high}}
#: {{uxi|tft|ngofa halal '''yang''' manyirah|t=the legitimate eldest son|lit=the legitimate son '''who is''' eldest}}
#: {{uxi|tft|oto '''yang''' ikuraci ngori ri die|t=the yellow car is mine|lit=the car '''which is''' yellow is my property}}
====Usage notes====
In older texts, as de Clercq mentions, ''yang'' was only used together with other Malay borrowings; in more recent usage, ''yang'' can follow non-Malay words as well.
